WEBVTT

00:04.281 --> 00:07.354
[JACK-IN-THE-BOX MELODY PLAYS]

00:07.357 --> 00:09.324
[SIZZLING]

00:13.363 --> 00:14.803
[EXPLOSION BOOMS]

00:14.806 --> 00:16.592
[CACKLING]

00:16.595 --> 00:18.076
Child's play!

00:19.703 --> 00:21.703
- [GLASS SHATTERING]
- Huh? Huh?!

00:21.705 --> 00:23.037
No!

00:23.040 --> 00:25.866
I will avenge you, my bulby brethren!

00:25.869 --> 00:28.417
Who would dare?

00:28.420 --> 00:29.911
[DARKWING DUCK] I am the terror

00:29.913 --> 00:31.713
that flaps in the night!

00:31.715 --> 00:32.781
[CHATTERING]

00:32.783 --> 00:34.783
I am the little roller skate

00:34.786 --> 00:37.496
at the base of villainy's staircase.

00:37.499 --> 00:41.306
I am Darkwing Duck!

00:41.309 --> 00:42.923
[QUARTERJACK] Playtime's over!

00:42.926 --> 00:44.920
Then I gotta get a shorter intro.

00:49.933 --> 00:52.467
Let's get dangerous.

00:53.670 --> 00:55.504
- [SIZZLING]
- [GRUNTING]

01:00.711 --> 01:02.577
[BOTH BLUBBERING]

01:04.882 --> 01:06.615
Big day, Dewey.

01:06.617 --> 01:08.326
Mustard stain or ketchup stain?

01:08.329 --> 01:10.039
Mustard... looks less like blood.

01:10.042 --> 01:11.485
What is this weird show?

01:11.488 --> 01:12.654
Whoa, what?

01:12.656 --> 01:13.613
<i>Darkwing Duck?</i>

01:13.616 --> 01:16.181
The greatest TV show of all time?

01:16.184 --> 01:18.250
Ha! Maybe when you were a kid.

01:18.253 --> 01:21.462
This hero guy doesn't fly
or shoot lasers or anything.

01:21.465 --> 01:23.565
That hero guy is Jim Starling.

01:23.568 --> 01:26.080
He was an old-school actor
who did all his own stunts.

01:26.083 --> 01:27.438
Sure, he got a little banged up

01:27.441 --> 01:28.769
in later seasons.

01:28.772 --> 01:31.150
<i>[GRUNTING] Keep rolling.</i>

01:31.153 --> 01:33.153
But that just made him even more heroic.

01:33.156 --> 01:35.256
Why didn't he just use CGI?

01:35.259 --> 01:36.993
[CHUCKLES] Real heroes don't need

01:36.996 --> 01:38.352
high-tech special effects

01:38.355 --> 01:40.363
or basic safety precautions.

01:40.366 --> 01:42.112
So, how do I look?

01:44.321 --> 01:46.154
Remember, Dewey, a true hero thinks

01:46.157 --> 01:47.676
with his gut or not at all.

01:47.679 --> 01:48.889
Right, D.W.?

01:48.892 --> 01:51.591
<i>Let's get dangerous.</i>

01:51.594 --> 01:53.196
What's the special occasion, anyway?

01:53.199 --> 01:55.145
I finally got my driver's license.

01:55.148 --> 01:56.665
- [ENGINE STARTS]
- Uh, wait, what?

01:56.667 --> 01:58.133
Aah!

02:01.472 --> 02:04.090
<i>♪ Life is like a hurricane ♪</i>

02:04.093 --> 02:06.640
<i>♪ Here in Duckburg ♪</i>

02:06.643 --> 02:09.478
<i>♪ Race cars, lasers, airplanes ♪</i>

02:09.479 --> 02:12.347
<i>♪ It's a duck-blur ♪</i>

02:12.349 --> 02:15.080
<i>♪ We might solve a mystery ♪</i>

02:15.083 --> 02:17.249
<i>♪ Or rewrite history ♪</i>

02:17.252 --> 02:19.846
<i>♪ Ducktales, whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:19.849 --> 02:23.491
<i>♪ Every day they're out
there making Ducktales ♪</i>

02:23.494 --> 02:25.126
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:25.129 --> 02:26.774
<i>♪ Tales of derring-do ♪</i>

02:26.777 --> 02:28.760
<i>♪ Bad and good-luck tales ♪</i>

02:28.763 --> 02:30.332
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:30.334 --> 02:33.235
<i>♪ D-d-danger lurks behind you ♪</i>

02:33.237 --> 02:35.627
<i>♪ There's a stranger out to find you ♪</i>

02:35.630 --> 02:36.527
<i>♪ What to do? ♪</i>

02:36.530 --> 02:39.208
<i>♪ Just grab on to some Ducktales ♪</i>

02:39.210 --> 02:40.475
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:40.477 --> 02:42.890
<i>♪ Every day they're out there ♪</i>

02:42.893 --> 02:44.340
<i>♪ Making Ducktales ♪</i>

02:44.343 --> 02:46.147
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:46.150 --> 02:48.515
<i>♪ Tales of daring bad and good ♪</i>

02:48.518 --> 02:51.119
<i>♪ Not phony tales or cottontails ♪</i>

02:51.121 --> 02:52.964
<i>- ♪ No, Ducktales! ♪
- ♪ Whoo-ooh! ♪</i>

02:52.967 --> 02:55.957
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
