02:59.923 --> 03:01.789
[SLOW MOTION YELLING]

03:03.133 --> 03:04.132
[GRUNTS]

03:04.134 --> 03:05.389
How have you been a driver

03:05.392 --> 03:06.619
without a driver's license?

03:06.622 --> 03:09.102
Hey, come on. I've got a
pilot's license, don't I?

03:09.105 --> 03:10.904
Wait, don't I?

03:10.907 --> 03:12.825
Ugh! Aren't you worried
Scrooge will find out?

03:12.828 --> 03:14.802
You kidding? I had them mail the license

03:14.805 --> 03:17.112
straight to him so
he'd be first to know.

03:17.114 --> 03:19.314
Ah, he's gonna be so proud of me.

03:19.316 --> 03:20.747
[CHUCKLES] Wow.

03:22.332 --> 03:23.785
[DEWEY] The Bin, The Bin, The Bin!

03:23.787 --> 03:24.786
Slow down!

03:24.788 --> 03:26.755
[TIRES SQUEALING]

03:28.305 --> 03:30.271
- [HEAVY BREATHING]
- I bet Mr. McD's got

03:30.274 --> 03:32.240
some kind of party
planned for my big day.

03:32.243 --> 03:33.528
Wouldn't want to ruin the...

03:33.530 --> 03:35.764
- [ELEVATOR DINGS]
- Surprise!

03:35.766 --> 03:37.432
Huh.

03:37.434 --> 03:39.303
Surprise!

03:41.337 --> 03:42.636
Supplies?

03:42.639 --> 03:45.407
Boy, he's really getting my hopes up.

03:45.410 --> 03:47.476
The payoff is gonna be amazing.

03:47.479 --> 03:49.367
Surprise!

03:49.370 --> 03:50.711
- Shh! Quiet.
- Shh!

03:50.714 --> 03:52.405
The Gearloose Monophonicrail

03:52.408 --> 03:54.882
converts aural input
into kinetic propulsion.

03:54.885 --> 03:55.884
[DEWEY AND LAUNCHPAD] Huh?

03:55.886 --> 03:57.819
Sound-powered train.

03:57.821 --> 03:59.502
- [BOTH] Buh.
- Ah, sorry, Mr. McD,

03:59.505 --> 04:01.260
but I thought you might wanna hear...

04:01.263 --> 04:03.296
I don't want to hear anything.

04:03.299 --> 04:06.400
This sensitive prototype runs on noise.

04:06.403 --> 04:07.502
Observe.

04:07.505 --> 04:09.472
[HUMMING]

04:13.243 --> 04:14.912
Illumination, Dr. Gearloose!

04:14.915 --> 04:16.398
Alphanumerical substitution!

04:16.401 --> 04:17.738
The categorical reorganization

04:17.741 --> 04:19.574
of letters to prime digits.

04:19.576 --> 04:21.442
[SIZZLING, WHIRRING]

04:23.346 --> 04:24.645
Aah! My blueprints!

04:29.425 --> 04:30.819
Sorry, Dr. Gearloose.

04:30.821 --> 04:32.754
Intern, try to think.

04:32.756 --> 04:34.592
But that's all I do all the time.

04:34.595 --> 04:35.724
Well, do it better.

04:35.726 --> 04:36.940
Eh, you probably couldn't fit a driver

04:36.942 --> 04:38.423
in that tiny train anyway.

04:38.426 --> 04:40.359
Uh, say, speaking of drivers...

04:40.362 --> 04:41.895
Gyro, the board needs results.

04:41.898 --> 04:43.631
Ever since Bulb Tech backfired

04:43.633 --> 04:45.734
you need an invention that, well...

04:45.736 --> 04:47.602
Won't turn evil and kill us all.

04:47.604 --> 04:50.259
Due respect, sir, innovation
doesn't work that way.

04:50.262 --> 04:51.994
I can't just wake up
one morning and say...

04:51.997 --> 04:53.502
How about a self-driving robot car?

04:53.505 --> 04:55.876
- A what, now?
- Wah! Too many variables.

04:55.879 --> 04:57.140
A self-driving robot car

04:57.143 --> 04:58.812
would turn evil like that.

04:58.815 --> 05:00.782
- Nobody could.
- Well, Mark Beaks did.

05:00.784 --> 05:02.684
He just posted that he's
having a demo later today.

05:02.686 --> 05:06.821
What?! That hack couldn't
even program a microwave!

05:06.823 --> 05:08.723
[CHUCKLES] We'll see about this.

05:08.725 --> 05:09.956
Okay, cool.

05:09.959 --> 05:11.923
I'll just tell you my big news later.

05:11.926 --> 05:14.562
Launchpad, I almost forgot...

05:14.564 --> 05:16.831
- Yeah?
- Stop having mail delivered to my office.

05:16.833 --> 05:18.967
That's for incoming checks
and death threats only.

05:24.441 --> 05:27.299
Wait, what does "Smiley
face, anvil, roadkill" mean?

05:27.302 --> 05:29.981
<i>- Crushed it!</i>
- [CROWD CHEERING]

05:29.984 --> 05:32.297
<i>It's a hectic world
posting things online,</i>

05:32.300 --> 05:34.200
<i>checking to see who liked your post.</i>

05:34.203 --> 05:36.416
<i>Couldn't you use a
little time for yourself?</i>

05:36.419 --> 05:39.554
<i>Couldn't you use a BUDDY?</i>

05:39.557 --> 05:43.108
<i>That's the "Beaks Unmanned
Driver Drone Yay!"</i>

05:43.111 --> 05:45.044
<i>BUDDY will drive you anywhere</i>

05:45.047 --> 05:47.859
<i>quickly, efficiently, and cheaply!</i>

05:49.866 --> 05:52.059
<i>BUDDY is compatible with any vehicle,</i>

05:52.062 --> 05:54.635
<i>making traditional drivers
a thing of the past.</i>

05:54.638 --> 05:55.870
<i>The Waddle BUDDY system.</i>

05:55.872 --> 05:57.872
<i>Because machines are the new man.</i>

05:57.874 --> 06:00.841
<i>And hold for applause!</i>

06:00.844 --> 06:02.254
- [APPLAUSE]
- Boo! Bad!

06:02.257 --> 06:03.824
- Do not like!
- Agreed.

06:03.827 --> 06:05.813
Very negative feelings, indeed.

06:05.816 --> 06:10.207
<i>Whoa, Scrooge's driver
and his chief inventor</i>

06:10.210 --> 06:12.888
<i>are threatened by my BUDDY here.</i>

06:12.891 --> 06:16.423
<i>Well, that is how you know
it's a good product. [LAUGHS]</i>

06:16.426 --> 06:18.938
- [CROWD MURMURING]
- Uh, how can you ensure

06:18.941 --> 06:21.662
that this machine won't turn evil?

06:21.665 --> 06:23.459
Huh. I've never said that out loud.

06:23.462 --> 06:25.694
<i>Top secret Beaks tech means</i>

06:25.697 --> 06:27.955
<i>this baby's 100% obedient to its master.</i>

06:27.958 --> 06:29.472
<i>- Next question, please.</i>
- Oh, yeah?

06:29.475 --> 06:30.788
Can you program a robot

06:30.791 --> 06:32.758
to brave the unknown
and laugh at danger?

06:32.761 --> 06:35.023
<i>- Yes.</i>
- Can a robot greet you

06:35.026 --> 06:37.444
with a kind word at
the end of a long day?

06:37.447 --> 06:39.256
<i>- Yes.</i>
- [BUDDY] <i>That's a nice</i>

06:39.259 --> 06:41.259
<i>gray cardigan, Mr. Beaks.</i>

06:41.262 --> 06:44.129
<i>You are killing it today.</i>

06:44.132 --> 06:46.432
Huh. Yeah, well, can a robot

06:46.435 --> 06:48.269
pull you from the wreckage of a crash

06:48.272 --> 06:50.656
with a reassuring smile that tells you

06:50.659 --> 06:52.974
everything's gonna be okay?

06:52.977 --> 06:56.731
<i>Well, no, because it can't crash.</i>

06:56.733 --> 06:58.466
Wait, what, now? I'm
sorry, what was that?

06:58.468 --> 07:00.401
<i>BUDDY, show him.</i>

07:07.710 --> 07:09.124
<i>[BEAKS] BUDDY's patented sensors</i>

07:09.127 --> 07:11.612
<i>mean a smooth, crash-free ride.</i>

07:11.615 --> 07:14.482
<i>No matter the situation,
you can count on BUDDY</i>

07:14.484 --> 07:16.772
<i>to get you where you're going safely.</i>

07:18.655 --> 07:20.040
<i>Any more questions?</i>

07:20.043 --> 07:21.513
This automated marvel could save

07:21.516 --> 07:23.592
McDuck Enterprises a fortune!

07:26.563 --> 07:28.727
You're not seriously gonna
buy one of these things.

07:28.730 --> 07:33.568
I mean, not when you have plenty
of good driver/pilots already.

07:33.570 --> 07:35.027
I may buy a whole fleet!

07:35.030 --> 07:37.371
Unless anyone has any brighter ideas.

07:37.374 --> 07:38.373
[GROANS]

07:38.375 --> 07:39.374
- A race.
- [BOTH GASP]

07:39.376 --> 07:40.300
What are you doing?

07:40.303 --> 07:41.607
Thinking with my gut.

07:41.610 --> 07:43.029
Me versus the bot.

07:43.032 --> 07:45.579
Winner gets free candy for life.

07:45.582 --> 07:47.913
- [INDISTINCT WHISPERS]
- Oh, that's better.

07:47.916 --> 07:50.618
Winner is named the ultimate driver.

07:50.620 --> 07:52.999
A race would give me a chance

07:53.002 --> 07:55.689
to see how BUDDY performs
in a real-world scenario.

07:55.692 --> 07:57.233
Ooh! Dramatic!

07:57.236 --> 07:58.369
In! In! In! In! In!

07:58.372 --> 08:01.173
May the best man...
Ooh! Aah! Robot hand!

08:01.176 --> 08:02.467
Very strong robot hand.

08:04.000 --> 08:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:18.802 --> 08:19.901
- Aah!
- Aah! Look out!

08:19.903 --> 08:21.086
It's a headless man-horse!

08:21.089 --> 08:22.803
He broke in to hoof us all to death!

08:22.806 --> 08:24.217
[GYRO] What?! Don't be dumb.

08:24.220 --> 08:25.872
I'm just trying out some new interns.

08:25.875 --> 08:27.742
Don't tell my existing intern.

08:27.744 --> 08:30.055
Manny, dispose of them violently.

08:30.058 --> 08:31.408
I can't have any distractions.

08:31.411 --> 08:32.879
No, wait. I need help.

08:32.881 --> 08:34.514
See, I have this friend.

08:34.517 --> 08:36.669
Let's call him, "Not Launchpad."

08:36.673 --> 08:39.034
And he kinda challenged
a robot to a race.

08:39.037 --> 08:40.274
Pretty common scenario.

08:40.277 --> 08:42.816
Now, Not Launchpad definitely

08:42.818 --> 08:44.274
isn't afraid of losing

08:44.277 --> 08:46.544
and his boss replacing him with a robot,

08:46.547 --> 08:48.849
but he has a friend...

08:48.852 --> 08:52.084
Let's call him, uh, "Launchpad"...

08:52.087 --> 08:54.241
Who <i>is</i> very worried about that.

08:54.244 --> 08:55.965
So, I... he... they...

08:55.968 --> 08:57.836
Uh, thought you could help

08:57.839 --> 09:00.990
figure out how to take
this robot down, yes?

09:02.185 --> 09:04.565
Oh, in this scenario, you're still you.

09:04.568 --> 09:07.469
Dummy! There's some
dummies here to see you.

09:07.472 --> 09:09.246
At your beck and call, Dr. Gearloose.

09:09.249 --> 09:11.632
I heard everything. Everything.

09:11.635 --> 09:14.160
I'm happy to prove my
worth by aiding Mr. McQuack.

09:14.163 --> 09:16.088
Dr. Gearloose is
working on an innovation

09:16.091 --> 09:17.623
that will better all of mankind

09:17.626 --> 09:19.360
both literally, and figuratively.

09:19.363 --> 09:21.196
Behold!

09:25.668 --> 09:26.801
Operating passcode:

09:26.803 --> 09:28.336
- Blathering...
- No!

09:29.112 --> 09:31.705
That... [CHUCKLES] is not ready yet.

09:31.708 --> 09:33.474
- Go to your room!
- Aah! Ohh.

09:33.476 --> 09:35.242
Forgive Dr. Gearloose.
He's a little more

09:35.245 --> 09:36.670
deranged than usual trying to figure out

09:36.672 --> 09:38.329
how Beaks beat him to
the self-driving car.

09:38.331 --> 09:39.659
That won't be a problem once

09:39.662 --> 09:41.676
I put that tin can in its place.

09:41.679 --> 09:44.090
In the recycling,
where the garbage goes.

09:44.093 --> 09:46.353
Woof. We'll work on smack talk later.

09:46.356 --> 09:47.286
Right now we need something

09:47.288 --> 09:48.895
to help Launchpad get the edge on BUDDY.

09:48.898 --> 09:50.762
Step into my laboratory.

09:51.828 --> 09:53.694
Your lab is in the bathroom?

09:53.696 --> 09:56.597
Dr. Gearloose says this is
the perfect place for my work.

09:56.599 --> 09:58.446
I'm just now realizing that remark

09:58.449 --> 10:00.081
may not have been
entirely complimentary.

10:00.084 --> 10:01.383
No matter!

10:01.386 --> 10:03.153
So, how are we going
to soup up your car?

10:03.156 --> 10:05.289
Frictionless tires?
Oscillating overthruster?

10:05.292 --> 10:07.909
An engine that can bend the
very fabric of space itself?

10:07.912 --> 10:09.002
Yes! All of that.

10:09.005 --> 10:10.434
Eh, I don't know

10:10.437 --> 10:12.169
about all these gizmos.

10:12.172 --> 10:13.677
Can't you just give me a couple pointers

10:13.679 --> 10:14.782
on how to beat that robot?

10:14.784 --> 10:16.784
Reprogramming a man's brain to compete

10:16.786 --> 10:18.686
with a sophisticated auto intelligence.

10:18.688 --> 10:20.262
Reprogram Launchpad?

10:20.265 --> 10:21.555
What about thinking with your gut

10:21.557 --> 10:22.556
and getting dangerous?

10:22.559 --> 10:24.245
Well, if Mr. McD thinks

10:24.248 --> 10:26.827
this un-crashable robo-me is so great,

10:26.830 --> 10:28.992
I have to prove I can get dangerous

10:28.995 --> 10:30.698
in the safest way possible.

10:30.700 --> 10:32.867
That's sure to get Dr.
Gearloose's attention.

10:32.869 --> 10:34.669
[INTERN] It could work!

10:34.671 --> 10:36.161
[SPLASHING]

10:36.164 --> 10:37.348
I'll clean that later.

10:40.216 --> 10:42.026
[INTERN] Don't go
over 32 miles per hour.

10:42.029 --> 10:44.044
And hit all turns at
a safe 35-degree bend.

10:44.047 --> 10:46.499
And increase velocity
by 15% on straightaway.

10:46.502 --> 10:47.735
These visual cues will trigger

10:47.738 --> 10:49.311
psychosomatic synaptic reflexes

10:49.314 --> 10:50.623
to improve your performance.

10:50.626 --> 10:51.681
Did you get all that?

10:53.437 --> 10:55.270
Yes.

10:55.273 --> 10:58.757
Welcome to the Waddle test track!

10:58.760 --> 11:00.479
Time for the ultimate contest

11:00.482 --> 11:02.112
between man and machine.

11:02.115 --> 11:03.563
First around the block wins.

11:03.566 --> 11:04.732
Don't worry, Mr. McD.

11:04.734 --> 11:06.173
- I got this.
- Good lad.

11:06.176 --> 11:07.563
Beat this bionic blackguard,

11:07.566 --> 11:09.516
and I can probably
talk Beaks down on price

11:09.519 --> 11:10.704
when I buy a fleet of them.

11:10.707 --> 11:12.540
Anyway, good luck!

11:12.542 --> 11:13.590
Hey, you're the best

11:13.593 --> 11:15.112
personal driver I've ever had.

11:15.115 --> 11:16.305
You got this!

11:16.308 --> 11:17.657
[INTERN] Follow the tips, and you have

11:17.659 --> 11:18.919
a 51% chance of winning.

11:18.922 --> 11:20.680
And whatever you do, play it safe.

11:20.683 --> 11:22.238
Don't crash!

11:22.241 --> 11:23.407
Wait, don't crash?

11:23.410 --> 11:26.378
Racers to your marks!

11:26.381 --> 11:28.348
<i>Let's get dangerous!</i>

11:33.696 --> 11:34.829
Get set...

11:34.831 --> 11:37.632
[IMITATES LASERS]

11:37.634 --> 11:38.599
Hmm?

11:40.403 --> 11:41.983
That means go!

11:50.747 --> 11:52.847
And we're off.

11:52.849 --> 11:54.815
Hands at ten and two.

11:54.817 --> 11:56.588
Keep it in first gear.

11:56.591 --> 11:59.619
Or was that hands at ten
and one and second gear?

11:59.622 --> 12:00.621
Where's the index?

12:01.658 --> 12:03.291
Oh, no!

12:06.285 --> 12:07.702
[BOTH] Don't crash. Don't crash!

12:11.801 --> 12:13.801
[GRUNTS]

12:13.803 --> 12:15.252
Gotta catch up!

12:21.844 --> 12:24.233
Uh, check your six. Carry the two.

12:24.236 --> 12:26.189
[GRUNTING] Huh?

12:27.684 --> 12:29.850
[PANTING] 17, other number, Q!

12:29.852 --> 12:33.169
[BUDDY] <i>Adjusting
for hazardous conditions.</i>

12:36.413 --> 12:37.491
[LAUNCHPAD GRUNTS]

12:42.432 --> 12:44.732
[LAUNCHPAD BLUBBERING]

12:44.734 --> 12:46.185
Whoa!

12:48.286 --> 12:49.437
[STRAINING, GRUNTS]

12:49.439 --> 12:50.871
Oh! He's gonna do it!

12:50.873 --> 12:52.807
Go, you bumblebee-like savant!

12:52.809 --> 12:54.114
- Go!
- [GROANS]

12:54.117 --> 12:57.511
Whoo!

12:57.513 --> 12:59.880
[GROANING]

12:59.882 --> 13:01.229
[GRUNTS]

13:01.232 --> 13:03.682
- [RACE HORN BLOWS]
- [SIGHS]

13:03.685 --> 13:06.005
Ha ha! Yes! Did it!

13:06.008 --> 13:08.308
Take that, everyone who's not me!

13:09.692 --> 13:12.197
Impressive display, Beaks.

13:12.200 --> 13:14.091
You have really built something here.

13:14.094 --> 13:16.391
[GYRO] Or did he? I couldn't be sure

13:16.394 --> 13:18.698
until I saw how it
performed under pressure.

13:18.701 --> 13:20.979
The precision, the deadly grace.

13:20.982 --> 13:23.950
Oh, yes, I've seen it before.

13:23.953 --> 13:25.519
Ha ha!

13:27.136 --> 13:29.643
Beaks Tech is actually Bulb Tech!

13:29.646 --> 13:31.060
That's how he beat me to the punch.

13:31.063 --> 13:32.712
He stole my technology!

13:32.715 --> 13:35.616
Officer, arrest this man!

13:35.618 --> 13:37.752
- Is this true?
- Of course not.

13:37.754 --> 13:39.220
I didn't steal it from him.

13:39.223 --> 13:40.854
I stole it from a public online forum,

13:40.857 --> 13:42.623
then "Beaks'd" it up.

13:42.625 --> 13:45.242
How would one of my inventions

13:45.245 --> 13:48.212
end up online? [GASPS]

13:48.215 --> 13:50.014
- Oh, wow!
- You!

13:50.017 --> 13:51.866
You circumvented the kill switch.

13:51.868 --> 13:54.120
Why didn't anyone else on the
message board figure that out?

13:54.122 --> 13:58.265
You posted my top-secret
plans on the Internet?!

13:58.268 --> 13:59.461
You were having so much trouble

13:59.463 --> 14:01.204
keeping your inventions
from turning evil,

14:01.207 --> 14:04.074
so I turned to the Net
to crowdsource a solution?

14:04.077 --> 14:05.778
Rah!

14:05.781 --> 14:07.548
- [INTERN BLUBBERING]
- [DEWEY] Easy! Easy!

14:07.550 --> 14:08.749
Gearloose, calm down!

14:08.751 --> 14:10.818
Fired!

14:10.820 --> 14:12.486
No.

14:15.825 --> 14:18.546
Uh, back to town, Mr. McD?

14:18.549 --> 14:19.980
That's all right, Launchpad.

14:19.983 --> 14:21.547
We'll ride with Beaks and BUDDY

14:21.550 --> 14:22.842
to sign the sales paperwork.

14:22.845 --> 14:23.967
Come on, Dewey.

14:26.669 --> 14:29.245
So, how did you keep
Bulb Tech from going bad?

14:29.248 --> 14:31.060
- Say what, now?
- The morality circuits.

14:31.063 --> 14:32.895
You modified them to
keep them from going evil.

14:32.897 --> 14:35.195
No, I just made them look less dorky.

14:35.198 --> 14:37.031
They're dumb robots, right?

14:37.034 --> 14:40.702
Oh, no. No, no, no,
no. No, no, no, no, no!

14:42.137 --> 14:43.799
[ALL SCREAMING]

14:47.495 --> 14:48.894
Room for one more?

14:50.233 --> 14:51.897
[BOTH SIGH]

14:51.899 --> 14:53.999
I have so many ideas, but I try too hard

14:54.001 --> 14:56.230
hoping at least one
of them will stand out.

14:56.233 --> 14:58.429
Just vomiting them out at random like,

14:58.432 --> 15:00.003
"Blah. Solve world hunger.

15:00.006 --> 15:01.766
Blah. Infrared toothbrush."

15:01.769 --> 15:03.635
I just wanna help people, you know?

15:03.638 --> 15:06.010
- [DISTANT SCREAMING]
- Make them better.

15:06.013 --> 15:08.032
Why? Even if you try to be better,

15:08.035 --> 15:09.775
there always someone better than you.

15:09.778 --> 15:11.900
Maybe with built-in Wi-Fi.

15:11.903 --> 15:13.225
You'll just be ignored.

15:13.228 --> 15:14.790
Best to stop trying.

15:16.397 --> 15:19.498
Man, is there anyone
having a worse day than us?

15:19.501 --> 15:21.368
[ALL SCREAMING]

15:21.371 --> 15:23.546
Churlish child locks!

15:23.549 --> 15:25.321
<i>Please remain seated.</i>

15:25.324 --> 15:27.691
Take that, you pneumatic monstrosity!

15:27.694 --> 15:29.566
<i>Buckle up for safety.</i>

15:29.569 --> 15:31.770
Sanctimonious seatbelts!

15:31.773 --> 15:34.194
Oh, we need a logic
puzzle to fry its circuits.

15:34.197 --> 15:36.761
- Uh, robot, what is love?
- That's stupid!

15:36.764 --> 15:38.226
Robot, could I invent an element

15:38.229 --> 15:40.321
so heavy even I couldn't lift it?

15:40.324 --> 15:41.914
[CHUCKLES] I definitely could.

15:41.916 --> 15:43.749
No, you couldn't!

15:43.751 --> 15:45.050
- Aah!
- [GASPS]

15:45.052 --> 15:46.739
Give it a rest, geniuses!

15:49.890 --> 15:51.340
[HORN BLOWING]

15:51.343 --> 15:53.992
Yes, you've replaced me
with a cool robot car.

15:53.995 --> 15:55.694
I get it.

15:55.696 --> 15:57.896
[GROUP SCREAMING]

15:58.966 --> 16:00.529
BUDDY's gone glitchy.

16:00.532 --> 16:01.967
- They're in trouble!
- What?

16:03.771 --> 16:06.473
I may not be Mr. McD's
driver for much longer,

16:06.476 --> 16:09.607
but he can still count on me
to get him where he's going.

16:09.610 --> 16:11.400
I'll keep him busy. You figure out a way

16:11.403 --> 16:12.680
to get them out of that car.

16:12.683 --> 16:14.194
I think I got something for that.

16:14.197 --> 16:16.096
You try corralling them
into a ravine, or...

16:16.099 --> 16:17.602
I'll probably just crash into it.

16:17.605 --> 16:19.279
[ENGINE REVS]

16:19.282 --> 16:20.647
Isn't that really, really unsafe?

16:20.650 --> 16:21.627
Tried playing it safe,

16:21.630 --> 16:23.606
old friend... didn't work.

16:24.758 --> 16:27.316
<i>- Let's get dangerous.</i>
- Let's get dangerous.

16:43.611 --> 16:45.264
<i>♪</i>

16:46.395 --> 16:47.746
Launchpad!

16:50.618 --> 16:52.015
Give me your hand!

16:52.018 --> 16:53.354
- [PHONE LINE RINGING]
- Come on!

16:53.357 --> 16:54.469
Pick up, pick up, pick up!

16:54.472 --> 16:55.705
[PHONE RINGING]

16:55.708 --> 16:57.608
[HOOF TAPPING] _

16:57.611 --> 16:59.151
Manny! Salvation!

16:59.154 --> 17:00.692
I know we've had our
differences in the past,

17:00.694 --> 17:01.919
but now we must put them aside

17:01.922 --> 17:03.848
for the greater good
of scientific endeavor.

17:03.851 --> 17:04.915
What say you?

17:04.919 --> 17:07.146
_

17:07.148 --> 17:10.117
It's me! Fenton Crackshell Cabrera.

17:10.119 --> 17:12.204
Just put the phone up to the floor!

17:16.683 --> 17:20.047
Operating passcode:
Blathering blatherskite!

17:24.018 --> 17:25.540
[LAUNCHPAD STRAINING]

17:27.074 --> 17:28.987
Manny, did anything happen?

17:28.989 --> 17:30.589
Whoa!

17:31.239 --> 17:32.645
<i>Please keep your hands and arms</i>

17:32.648 --> 17:34.929
<i>inside the vehicle at all times.</i>

17:39.867 --> 17:40.945
[GRUNTS]

17:44.263 --> 17:45.537
Aah!

17:47.769 --> 17:48.907
Dewey!

17:52.012 --> 17:54.680
[SCREAMING]

17:57.224 --> 17:59.358
- [GASPS]
- Gotcha!

18:07.762 --> 18:09.584
[LAUGHS] Wow!

18:11.932 --> 18:13.969
Hold on, I'll get you
out of here... somehow.

18:13.972 --> 18:15.710
Oh, good, another robot.

18:15.713 --> 18:17.969
[SUIT] <i>Calculating options.</i>

18:17.972 --> 18:20.572
<i>Activating shoulder blades.</i>

18:20.574 --> 18:22.941
I suggest you hold very, very still.

18:22.943 --> 18:24.605
[SCROOGE GROANING]

18:24.608 --> 18:25.944
Oh, hey!

18:25.946 --> 18:27.846
[BEAKS, GYRO EXCLAIM]

18:27.848 --> 18:30.042
- [SUIT BUZZES]
- Come on!

18:33.788 --> 18:35.256
[SUIT] <i>Incoming threat.</i>

18:35.259 --> 18:37.293
Come on, suit, do something!

18:37.296 --> 18:39.429
<i>Defense mode activated.</i>

18:40.895 --> 18:42.594
Whoa, look out!

18:49.744 --> 18:51.516
[SCROOGE] Who the blazes are you?

18:51.519 --> 18:52.937
Call me...

18:52.940 --> 18:54.977
Gizmoduck!

18:54.980 --> 18:57.583
- Gizmoduck?
- Gizmoduck.

18:59.038 --> 19:00.927
Suit, make it stop. Make it stop!

19:02.009 --> 19:03.189
Suit, help!

19:03.192 --> 19:06.193
<i>Activating gluteal grapple.</i>

19:06.196 --> 19:08.223
Ack, miss! Uh, something else!

19:08.226 --> 19:10.648
<i>Activating pectoral parachute.</i>

19:11.859 --> 19:14.162
[GIZMODUCK] Stop, stop!

19:16.483 --> 19:18.316
Brakes! Brakes!

19:18.319 --> 19:20.686
Aah!

19:20.689 --> 19:22.489
Huh?

19:27.608 --> 19:29.708
- [GASPING]
- You were a robot this whole time, huh?

19:29.711 --> 19:31.144
- Neat.
- I'm not a...

19:31.147 --> 19:32.792
<i>Warning, incoming threat.</i>

19:34.055 --> 19:35.254
Move!

19:35.257 --> 19:37.090
[TIRES SQUEAL]

19:50.409 --> 19:51.663
- Aah!
- Aah!

19:53.483 --> 19:55.834
[TIRES SCREECHING]

20:02.417 --> 20:04.447
<i>For your safety, please stop the vehicle</i>

20:04.450 --> 20:06.057
<i>and return to the passenger seat.</i>

20:06.060 --> 20:09.239
Looks like the only way
to survive is to crash.

20:09.242 --> 20:11.047
Too dangerous! Too dangerous!

20:20.488 --> 20:21.520
[ALL LAUGHING]

20:21.523 --> 20:23.052
Take that, you bucket of bolts.

20:23.055 --> 20:24.896
Oh, I'm sorry, is that offensive, or...

20:24.899 --> 20:26.565
- I'm not a...
- [ROCKS CRUMBLING]

20:28.836 --> 20:30.757
[ALL SCREAMING]

20:30.760 --> 20:34.343
[SUIT] <i>Activate helmet-copter.</i>

20:34.346 --> 20:36.446
[LAUGHS] Whoo-ooh!

20:36.449 --> 20:38.805
I'm alive! This is awesome!

20:38.808 --> 20:41.907
Aww, looks like somebody's first crash.

20:51.411 --> 20:53.095
Have a good day, Mr. McD.

20:53.098 --> 20:54.248
Nice work today, Launchpad.

20:54.251 --> 20:55.201
See you tomorrow.

20:55.204 --> 20:57.371
You're not gonna replace me?

20:57.374 --> 20:59.545
Replace you? Don't be daft.

20:59.548 --> 21:00.615
Where would I ever find a driver

21:00.617 --> 21:03.031
as crazy and dangerous as I am?

21:03.034 --> 21:06.365
Oh! Dewey told me about
your driver's license.

21:06.368 --> 21:08.368
Congratulations.

21:08.371 --> 21:10.204
[GRUNTS]

21:10.207 --> 21:13.308
Aww, your approval is all
the driver's license I need.

21:13.311 --> 21:15.311
Come on. [STRAINING]

21:15.314 --> 21:17.812
You should really keep the license.

21:21.055 --> 21:23.312
Sir, I was cleaning out my desk

21:23.315 --> 21:24.648
when suddenly the prototype armor

21:24.651 --> 21:27.058
burst from the chamber like
so many split atoms, and...

21:27.061 --> 21:29.443
Eh, save it. You're not fired...

21:29.446 --> 21:31.090
Gizmoduck.

21:31.093 --> 21:33.213
[SIGHS] Scrooge is always complaining

21:33.216 --> 21:35.066
my inventions are dangerous.

21:35.069 --> 21:37.171
This armor's gotta be 100% idiot proof,

21:37.174 --> 21:39.241
and, well, you're just
the idiot to prove it.

21:39.244 --> 21:41.439
Oh, thank you, sir!
You won't regret this.

21:41.442 --> 21:43.626
This project stays top
secret till it's out of beta.

21:43.629 --> 21:44.962
I won't tell a soul.

21:44.965 --> 21:46.343
[LAUNCHPAD] Bye, Gyro!

21:46.346 --> 21:47.503
Bye, Gizmoduck!

21:47.506 --> 21:48.909
From now on.

21:48.912 --> 21:51.309
[SIGHS] Gizmoduck.

21:51.312 --> 21:52.910
What a stupid name.

21:56.350 --> 22:00.017
Gizmoduck... I must have him.

